div.p:
“Concerned by the fact that many cases are still pending,
though they secured the supporting votes of seven or more of the members of the
    SC;

“Considering that notwithstanding the efforts that have
been made for some years, it has not as yet been possible to solve the important
problem of the admission of new members to the UN;

“Recalling that various states members of the UN have made specific proposals or put forward
suggestions with a view to reaching a satisfactory solution of the problem of
admission;

“Bearing in mind that the applications for admission of a
large number of states are still pending, despite the fact that seven or more
votes were cast in favour of the admission of many of them in the SC;
